Think about it.

32
00:03:21,630 --> 00:03:23,780
那已经不是几个细胞
That's not a few cells

33
00:03:24,140 --> 00:03:26,180
或一团组织那么大了
or a collection of cells.

34
00:03:26,180 --> 00:03:29,100
差不多已经有四英寸半大小
It's more like four and a half inches long

35
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:31,290
3.5盎司[约100克]那么重了
and three and a half ounces.

36
00:03:31,350 --> 00:03:33,560
16周的时候
At 16 weeks,

37
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:36,500
总统的胎儿应该已经有
the President's baby would have been the size...

38
00:03:37,730 --> 00:03:38,760
这么大了
of this.

39
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:42,360
美国同胞们  当前有一些人
My fellow Americans, there are certain parties out there

40
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:46,430
希望利用我的个人生活攫取政治利益
that hope to use my private life for political gain.

41
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:49,470
下面的话  我只说一次
I'm going to say this exactly once.

42
00:03:49,910 --> 00:03:53,140
多年来我和我已故的丈夫一直在尝试组建家庭
For many years, my late husband and I tried to start a family.

43
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:57,020
我从前之所以不怎么提这事  是因为
I downplayed that fact in the past because...

44
00:03:57,540 --> 00:03:59,650
这是一个痛苦的话题
Well, it's a painful subject.

45
00:04:01,010 --> 00:04:03,240
当我终于怀孕的时候
When I finally became pregnant,

46
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:05,700
孩子却发育不良
the baby wasn't viable,

47
00:04:05,930 --> 00:04:08,300
所以不得不终止妊娠
and the pregnancy had to be terminated.

48
00:04:08,310 --> 00:04:09,580
仅此而已
End of story.

49
00:04:12,100 --> 00:04:13,710
孩子是健康孩子
The baby was viable.

50
00:04:14,230 --> 00:04:17,340
但我和弗兰西斯  不是好父母
Francis and I, as parents, were not.

51
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:20,670
我要说清楚
So, let me be clear.

52
00:04:21,490 --> 00:04:26,390
这将是我最后一次谈及这个话题
This is the last I will ever say on this subject.

53
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:28,100
好了
Okay.

54
00:04:40,210 --> 00:04:43,920
今天在座的各位  都让我非常骄傲
I am so proud of every person around this table.

55
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:46,130
她们每一个人都服务国家多年
Each of them has served this country

56
00:04:46,130 --> 00:04:48,430
兢兢业业  忠于职守
with honor and distinction.

57
00:04:48,430 --> 00:04:50,620
有些已经位列副部
Some as deputy secretaries.

58
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:54,350
她们都是美国人中的佼佼者
They are all accomplished Americans

59
00:04:54,350 --> 00:04:57,290
在各自部门和领域中成就卓著
and members of their respective departments.

60
00:04:58,230 --> 00:05:00,590
不过还是由她们介绍自己吧
But I'll let them speak for themselves.

61
00:05:02,320 --> 00:05:05,400
大家好  我是珍妮佛·邦加顿
Hello, my name is Jennifer Baumgarten,

62
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:08,590
担任代理联邦检察官
and I am the acting Attorney General of the United States.

63
00:05:09,950 --> 00:05:12,390
珍妮会帮我大忙的
Jenny's going to come in very handy.

64
00:05:12,580 --> 00:05:15,770
就司法部而言
And as far as the Justice Department is concerned,

65
00:05:15,870 --> 00:05:19,940
我也认同总统清理门户的努力
I share the President's commitment to cleaning house.

66
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:22,550
可是副总统出席所有内阁会议
But isn't it customary for the vice president

67
00:05:22,550 --> 00:05:24,340
不是惯例吗
to attend all cabinet meetings?

68
00:05:24,340 --> 00:05:25,860
并不是必须出席
Not necessarily, no.

69
00:05:26,930 --> 00:05:30,050
是这样  自从我加入安德伍德政府
Listen, ever since I joined the Underwood administration,

70
00:05:30,050 --> 00:05:32,510
总统和我始终合作紧密  信任无间
the President and I have worked together on a daily basis.

71
00:05:32,510 --> 00:05:34,270
配合默契  我们就是这样
Hand in glove. That's the way we work.

72
00:05:34,270 --> 00:05:36,270
你被要求辞职是真的吗
Is it true that you were asked to resign?

73
00:05:36,270 --> 00:05:37,460
什么  当然没有
What? No.

74
00:05:38,020 --> 00:05:38,880
没有
No.

75
00:05:39,690 --> 00:05:42,400
至于我通俄的指控  更是荒唐
And the Russians and me, it's preposterous.

76
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:45,470
我和总统都同意
Look, the President and I agree

77
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:48,150
揪出这些不实指控背后主谋的最好办法
the best way to find out who's behind these accusations

78
00:05:48,150 --> 00:05:50,260
就是任命一位特别检察官
is to appoint a special prosecutor.

79
00:05:50,660 --> 00:05:52,930
让他或她依法履职
And let him or her do her job.

80
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:55,560
-非常感谢  -再问一个问题  一个问题
- Thanks very much. - One more question, one question!

81
00:05:55,790 --> 00:05:57,250
