多少钱
How much is that?

100
00:06:43,540 --> 00:06:46,820
首张一块九  续张每张一块二毛五
$1.90 for the first page, $1.25 for each additional.

101
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:50,130
看起来你续张可不少呢
And it looks like you've got quite a few additionals coming in.

102
00:06:50,130 --> 00:06:51,090
我能不能...
But can I just...

103
00:06:51,090 --> 00:06:53,340
让我算算一共要花多少钱
Let me just figure out how much it's gonna cost.

104
00:06:53,350 --> 00:06:54,390
这些钱足够了
That's more than enough.

105
00:06:54,390 --> 00:06:55,490
是啊  谢谢你
Yeah, thank you.

106
00:07:06,690 --> 00:07:07,550
给你
Here you go.

107
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,590
-谢谢  -客气
- Thank you. - You bet.

108
00:07:57,410 --> 00:07:59,220
39.3度
102.7.

109
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:01,060
你干吗让护士走
Why did you send the nurse away?

110
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:04,020
因为她也得吃饭
Because she needed to eat.

111
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:06,230
而且我感觉还行
And I feel fine.

112
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:10,030
-我看你还行才怪  -不不  你看
- I find this anything but fine. - No, no, look...

113
00:08:11,260 --> 00:08:12,670
发烧是好事
This fever's good.

114
00:08:12,670 --> 00:08:14,860
但我觉得不该烧这么久
I don't think it's supposed to last this long.

115
00:08:16,930 --> 00:08:18,530
要我给你换床单吗
Do you want me to change the sheets?

116
00:08:22,310 --> 00:08:23,460
反正还会湿的
What's the point?

117
00:08:26,190 --> 00:08:28,420
你知道我无论如何都支持你
You know, I support you no matter what.

118
00:08:29,270 --> 00:08:31,010
不管你想尝试什么疗法
Whatever you want to try,

119
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:32,970
但是这也...
but this is...

120
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:34,930
研究成果很乐观
Research is very good.

121
00:08:35,860 --> 00:08:37,470
在欧洲也临床验证过了
Proven effective in Europe.

122
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:49,230
你还记得
Do you remember

123
00:08:50,380 --> 00:08:54,280
老爸总是逼我穿长袖吃晚餐吗
how dad used to make me wear long sleeves at dinner?

124
00:08:56,470 --> 00:08:57,490
你想他们吗
Do you miss them?

125
00:08:59,430 --> 00:09:02,160
想妈  不想他
Her, not him.

126
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:07,710
他总是对是非对错那么笃定
He was always so sure about what was right.

127
00:09:08,690 --> 00:09:14,300
妈妈的疑虑经年累月  反倒让她更深刻了
Mom's doubt actually allowed her to deepen as time went by.

128
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:17,130
深刻也没那么好
Depth is overrated.

129
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:23,520
明天要不要取消
Do you want to cancel tomorrow?

130
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:27,520
怎么能取消呢
We can't cancel.

131
00:09:31,750 --> 00:09:33,030
怎么了  安妮
What's wrong, Annie?

132
00:09:35,970 --> 00:09:36,780
安妮
Annie?

133
00:09:41,010 --> 00:09:42,700
我一直打邓肯的电话
I keep calling Duncan.

134
00:09:45,310 --> 00:09:48,370
他不回话  也不回家
And I've heard nothing, and he still hasn't gone home.

135
00:09:52,190 --> 00:09:54,920
你知道他早晚会发现的
You knew he was gonna find out someday.

136
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:58,220
也许这样最好
Maybe it's for the best.

137
00:10:00,570 --> 00:10:02,490
如果您饿了渴了
If you're hungry or thirsty...

138
00:10:02,490 --> 00:10:05,270
我生气  累  还难过
Angry. Tired. Frustrated.

139
00:10:08,370 --> 00:10:10,250
我现在应该接受询问了
I should've been debriefed by now.

140
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:12,840
如果您需要水或者咖啡的话
Again, if you need water or a cup of coffee...

141
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:14,650
这太荒唐了
This is ridiculous.

142
00:10:15,380 --> 00:10:16,440
失陪下
Excuse me.

143
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:35,400
没有可见的伤痕
No visible scars.

144
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:39,470
看来你已经看过医生了
I assume you've been looked at by a physician.

145
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:40,970
这是程序
It's protocol.

146
00:10:41,910 --> 00:10:45,140
和局里高层联络也是
So is talking with a senior member of the Agency.

147
00:10:46,370 --> 00:10:48,180
今天你是见不着他们了
That won't be happening today.

148
00:10:49,410 --> 00:10:52,150
你基本上  废了
You're essentially burnt

149
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:55,150
不管是你和哪个情报局的工作
when it comes to your work with any of the agencies.

150
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:57,130
是这么说的吧  "废了"
That's the term, isn't it, burnt?

151
00:10:57,130 --> 00:10:58,260
不非得这么说
Not necessarily.

152
00:10:58,260 --> 00:10:59,990
差不多都这么说
Virtually always.

153
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:03,840
没人知道你被监禁期间说了什么  没说什么
Nobody knows what you said or didn't say while in captivity.

154
00:11:03,850 --> 00:11:05,610
我没说  克莱尔
I didn't say, Claire.

155
00:11:05,610 --> 00:11:07,200
是总统女士
Madam President.

156
00:11:09,890 --> 00:11:11,460
你听说马克的事了吗
Oh, and have you heard about Mark?

157
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:15,500
他把自己变成了一出好戏
He's made quite a spectacle of himself.

158
00:11:15,570 --> 00:11:18,110
也许过不了多久  我就不得不发话了
I don't know how much longer I can keep my voice out of it.

159
00:11:18,110 --> 00:11:20,630
我猜他是以为他可以全身而退
I guess he thought he could come out from under it.

160
00:11:21,910 --> 00:11:24,530
是啊  那些最了解我们的人
Yes. Well, the people that know us best,

161
00:11:24,530 --> 00:11:26,470
也最知道怎么伤害我们
know best how to hurt us.

162
00:11:31,210 --> 00:11:32,620
安德伍德总统
President Underwood...

163
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:34,610
其实我已经改回娘家姓黑尔了
Actually, I've gone back to "Hale."

164
00:11:36,170 --> 00:11:37,750
你错了  如果你认为我参与了...
You're wrong if you think I have...

165
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:40,950
你不告诉我实情  就太傻了
You are foolish if you don't tell me what it is.

166
00:11:46,390 --> 00:11:49,500
猜猜我不想再忍受哪种人了  简
Guess which kind of people I'm done suffering, Jane.

167
00:12:08,910 --> 00:12:10,350
你是来对了
You were wise to come.

168
00:12:11,540 --> 00:12:13,310
我告诉过你了  我也会告诉他们
I told you and I'll tell them.

169
00:12:13,830 --> 00:12:15,270
我不想要这份工作
I don't want the job.

170
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:21,820
道格  你决定前  务必听他们说完
Doug, just promise you'll hear them out before you do anything.

171
00:12:22,170 --> 00:12:25,450
而且提醒你一句  比尔现在不跟人握手
And just so you're aware, Bill's not shaking hands at the moment.

172
00:12:29,810 --> 00:12:32,290
道格  给你介绍一下
Doug. May I introduce you?

173
00:12:32,810 --> 00:12:34,850
安奈特和比尔·谢泼德
Annette and Bill Shepherd.

174
00:12:34,850 --> 00:12:35,920
你好
Hello.

175
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:38,710
你还认得弗莱德·安博格吧
You remember Fred Amburg.

176
00:12:39,610 --> 00:12:40,800
道格  说真的
Doug, for the record,

177
00:12:41,190 --> 00:12:43,820
我很喜欢在疗养院和你聊天
I really enjoyed our conversations in the facility.

178
00:12:43,820 --> 00:12:44,840
行了
Come on, man.

179
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:47,600
条条大路通罗马
All roads lead to Rome, you know?

180
00:12:47,990 --> 00:12:49,560
安奈特和比尔就是罗马
And Annette and Bill are Rome.

181
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:53,140
来请坐吧  斯坦普先生
Come. Sit down, please, Mr. Stamper.

182
00:12:53,540 --> 00:12:54,940
他们正要走
These guys were just leaving.

183
00:12:56,540 --> 00:12:57,770
再会了  谢泼德先生
